title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith & Wesson .38/44 Heavy Duty Transitional model
postcontent: LOCAL SALE ONLY!  DON'T ASK IF I'LL SHIP.For sale is my prized S&W .38/44 Heavy Duty.  I'm freeing up some cash to purchase some youth model guns for my kids.  This is an N Frame gun that has NOT been rechambered to 357 magnum.  It's still just a beefed up 38 Special.  This is a transitional model destinguished by pre-war characteristics as well as those from later models.  Only about 2500 of these were made from 1946 to 1950.  These are the shortest run of HDs.  This example has the long throw hammer but has the four-line address on the frame.  It probably left the factory sometime in '49.  Overall the exterior finish is worn and shows what I think is extended holster wear/storage.  The finish is thinning but the pictures don't show how dark the finish still is.  There is no pitting that I can find.  Internal parts look new.  There's even a little case color still present on the serrated trigger.  I've installed one .002 inch end shake bearing and had the hand replaced by Gunsmithing Only.  Lock-up is like a bank vualt now.  It's tighter than when my modern 629 was new.  Timing is great and it's a very good shooter.  The grips are Magnas but not correct ones.  All serial numbers match except the grips.  I am letting this go for less than I have in it.  I'm not really interested in trades but might consider some offers.  I'd be interested in a nice S&W 28-2 Highway Patrolman with 6 inch barrel or a 625 Mountain Gun in 45 Colt.  A Glock G40 in good shape would be interesting too.  I can email more pictures if necessary.  Please feel free to ask questions.Again, I WILL NOT ship this revolver.  I'm willing to meet in Topeka, KC area or Wichita but my schedule is tight.
